HEADWORD: Bouillon
<hw>Bou`illon"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>bouillir</ets> to boil.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A nutritious liquid
food made by boiling beef, or other meat, in water; a clear soup or
broth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>An excrescence on a horse's frush
or frog.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bouk</ent>⟦br⟧
